Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is the softmax function?
AI Response

Softmax converts a vector of raw scores (logits) into probabilities that sum to 1, typically used as the final
activation in multi-class classification models.

Example 1.2

User

What is dropout?
AI Response

Dropout randomly sets a fraction of neuron activations to zero during training, preventing co-adaptation of
neurons and reducing overfitting.

Example 1.3

User

What is reinforcement learning?
AI Response

Reinforcement learning trains an agent to make decisions by interacting with an environment and receiving
rewards or penalties, aiming to maximize cumulative reward over time.

Example 1.4

User

What is zero-shot learning?
AI Response

Zero-shot learning predicts unseen classes by leveraging semantic relationships or natural language task
descriptions, allowing LLMs to generalize without task-specific training.

Example 1.5

User

What is fine-tuning?
AI Response

Fine-tuning updates a pre-trained model's weights on a smaller, task-specific dataset. It is more efficient than
training from scratch and achieves strong performance with limited data.

Example 1.6

User

What is gradient descent?
AI Response

Gradient descent is an optimization algorithm that iteratively adjusts model parameters in the direction
opposite to the gradient of the loss function to find a minimum.

Example 1.7

User

What is transfer learning?
AI Response



Transfer learning reuses a model trained on one task as a starting point for another related task, reducing
training time and data requirements significantly.

Example 1.8

User

What is batch normalization?
AI Response

Batch normalization normalizes layer inputs to have zero mean and unit variance, stabilizing training,
reducing initialization sensitivity, and acting as a mild regularizer.

Example 1.9

User

What is an RNN?
AI Response

A Recurrent Neural Network processes sequential data with loops allowing information to persist. LSTMs and
GRUs are variants that address the vanishing gradient problem.

Example 1.10

User

What is a transformer model?
AI Response

A transformer is a deep learning architecture using self-attention mechanisms that process all tokens in
parallel, enabling efficient NLP. GPT and BERT are transformer-based models.



